WEBVTT

00:02.168 --> 00:06.297
[ "WINTER WONDERLAND"
INSTRUMENTAL PLAYS ]

00:14.139 --> 00:15.557
[ SIGHS ]

00:28.987 --> 00:30.864
CLAY,
I CANNOT DRIVE SAFELY

00:30.947 --> 00:33.908
IF YOU KEEP DISTRACTING ME
THIS WAY.

00:33.992 --> 00:35.952
CHEESE AND CRACKERS,
WILLIE RAY!

00:36.035 --> 00:39.622
YOU KNOW ONLY ONE THING GETS ME
IN THE HOLIDAY SPIRIT.

00:39.706 --> 00:42.917
WELL, YOUR PERRY COMO CDs DIDN'T
JUST GET UP AND WALK AWAY.

00:43.001 --> 00:45.170
THEY'VE GOT TO BE HERE
SOMEWHERE.

00:45.253 --> 00:47.964
WHY DON'T WE ALL SING
SOME CAROLS?

00:48.047 --> 00:50.425
WOULDN'T THAT BE FUN?

00:50.508 --> 00:54.971
♪ O COME,
ALL YE FAITHFUL ♪

00:55.054 --> 00:58.141
♪ JOYFUL AND TRIUMPHANT ♪

00:58.224 --> 01:03.021
♪ O COME YE, O COME YE ♪

01:03.104 --> 01:06.232
♪ TO BETHLEHEM ♪

01:06.316 --> 01:07.817
COME ON, EVERYBODY!

01:07.901 --> 01:12.238
♪ COME AND BEHOLD HIM ♪

01:12.322 --> 01:15.074
♪ BORN THE KING OF ANGELS ♪

01:15.158 --> 01:16.743
THERE'S NOT
MUCH TRAFFIC TODAY.

01:16.826 --> 01:18.787
WE'RE MAKING
AWFULLY GOOD TIME.

01:21.414 --> 01:22.874
Willie Ray:
♪ O COME LET US ADORE... ♪

01:22.957 --> 01:25.084
YOU KNOW WHAT I KEEP
THINKING ABOUT?

01:25.168 --> 01:28.004
THAT OLD GUARD THAT DIED.

01:28.087 --> 01:29.839
WHAT WAS HIS NAME?

01:29.923 --> 01:31.800
ARNIE, I THINK.

01:31.883 --> 01:33.676
RIGHT.
ARNIE, ARNIE, ARNIE.

01:33.760 --> 01:35.887
THE ONE WHO TOLD WESLEY
TO STAY INSIDE

01:35.970 --> 01:39.015
WHEN HIS FRIENDS WERE
SHOOTING UP THAT ARMORED CAR.

01:41.476 --> 01:44.187
DID Y'ALL EVER TALK?

01:44.270 --> 01:46.022
ARNIE WAS
A NICE OLDER GUY.

01:46.105 --> 01:48.691
HAD A FAMILY
THAT LOVED HIM.

01:48.775 --> 01:50.527
[ SIGHS ]

01:50.610 --> 01:51.861
WAS ARNIE EVER RUDE
TO YOU, WESLEY?

01:51.945 --> 01:53.655
I WANT TO SPEAK
TO MY BROTHER.

01:53.738 --> 01:55.448
YOU'RE SO CONCERNED
ABOUT YOUR BROTHER'S WELFARE,

01:55.532 --> 01:56.741
WHY DID YOU RUN AWAY,

01:56.825 --> 01:59.744
LEAVE HIM ALONE
IN A CITY HE BARELY KNEW

01:59.828 --> 02:01.579
THOUSANDS OF MILES
FROM HOME?

02:01.663 --> 02:04.499
YOU MUST HAVE FELT
YOU WERE IN DANGER OF SOME KIND.

02:04.582 --> 02:07.043
PLEASE. I'M --
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

02:07.126 --> 02:08.711
I'M BEGGING YOU, OKAY?

02:08.795 --> 02:11.714
JUST -- JUST FIVE MINUTES
WITH HIM ON THE PHONE.

02:11.798 --> 02:14.342
HE'S GONNA BE FREAKED OUT
NOT HEARING FROM ME.

02:14.425 --> 02:16.177
YOU WANT TO FIND OUT
WHAT'S GOING ON WITH GRADY,

02:16.261 --> 02:18.263
YOU TALK TO<i> ME</i> FIRST.

02:18.346 --> 02:19.514
WAIT.

02:21.808 --> 02:23.893
I NEED TO USE
THE TOILET.

02:27.856 --> 02:29.357
LIEUTENANT.

02:32.861 --> 02:34.946
COME ON.

02:37.824 --> 02:40.159
FAR AS I GO.

02:41.536 --> 02:44.122
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

02:45.999 --> 02:47.208
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

02:47.292 --> 02:48.209
HELLO?

02:48.293 --> 02:49.168
HELLO, CHIEF.

02:49.252 --> 02:51.462
Am I on speakerphone?

02:51.546 --> 02:52.797
NO.

02:54.173 --> 02:57.260
OH, GOOD. LIEUTENANT TAO,
DO WE HAVE OUR WARRANT?

02:57.343 --> 02:59.387
UH, NO,
BUT HERE'S THE GOOD NEWS.

02:59.470 --> 03:01.097
When Wesley Reed
was charged with possession,

03:01.180 --> 03:02.974
HE AGREED TO ATTEND
A DIVERSION PROGRAM

03:03.057 --> 03:05.268
AS PART OF HIS SENTENCING,
BUT HE DIDN'T FINISH IT.

03:05.351 --> 03:07.437
AS SOON AS YOU GET HIM
BACK TO CALIFORNIA,
YOU CAN ARREST HIM.

03:07.520 --> 03:09.522
I STILL DON'T HAVE
THE PAPERWORK I NEED

03:09.606 --> 03:11.399
to bring him
across state lines.

03:11.482 --> 03:12.984
[ Sighs ]

03:13.067 --> 03:16.112
LOOK, NO MATTER WHAT, DON'T PUT
ME ON THE PHONE WITH CHIEF POPE.

03:16.195 --> 03:19.240
IF Y'ALL NEED TO CALL ME, JUST
CALL ME FROM YOUR CELLPHONES.

03:19.324 --> 03:20.575
Any news on the shooters?

03:20.658 --> 03:21.784
THE SHOOTERS.

03:21.868 --> 03:22.785
OH.

03:22.869 --> 03:24.370
YEAH, CHIEF --
UH, SORRY.

03:24.454 --> 03:25.955
AS FAR
AS KNOWN ASSOCIATES,

03:26.039 --> 03:29.250
NOTHING'S COME UP YET ON
EITHER NICKNAME GRADY GAVE US.

03:29.334 --> 03:31.127
TELL HER
ABOUT THE GETAWAY CAR.

03:31.210 --> 03:32.962
THIS CREW'S
THREE PREVIOUS ROBBERIES --

03:33.046 --> 03:35.965
TWICE THEY USED AN ASTRO VAN,
AND ONCE A CHEVY SUBURBAN.

03:36.049 --> 03:37.926
These are not rare vehicles,
Detective.

03:38.009 --> 03:40.470
WELL, THAT'S PROBABLY
WHY THEY USE THEM, CHIEF.

03:40.553 --> 03:43.264
Ask her about Pope.
About Pope.

03:43.348 --> 03:46.851
HOLD ON. SERGEANT GABRIEL
WANTS TO TALK TO YOU.

03:46.935 --> 03:48.728
[ SIGHS ]

03:48.811 --> 03:51.314
SO, UH, WHAT DO YOU WANT ME
TO TELL POPE?

03:51.397 --> 03:53.650
WELL, TELL HIM I'M HAVING
EXTRADITION PROBLEMS

03:53.733 --> 03:55.735
AND I'LL CALL HIM
WHEN I HAVE SOME NEWS.

03:55.818 --> 03:57.111
WHAT DOES GRADY SAY?

03:57.195 --> 03:59.322
WELL, CHIEF, IF HE KNOWS
ANYTHING ABOUT OUR SHOOTERS

03:59.405 --> 04:01.240
OTHER THAN THEIR NICKNAME,
HE'S NOT TELLING.

04:01.324 --> 04:02.659
[ SCOFFS ]
WELL, WHERE IS HE NOW?

04:02.742 --> 04:03.743
IN YOUR OFFICE.

04:03.826 --> 04:05.536
Put him in my house,
please,

04:05.620 --> 04:07.789
BEFORE SOMEBODY NOTICES
HE'S NOT IN FOSTER CARE.

04:07.872 --> 04:09.791
And try and get him
to talk to you.

04:09.874 --> 04:13.795
CHIEF, CHIEF.
LET SANCHEZ HAVE A GO AT HIM.

04:13.878 --> 04:14.921
OH!

04:16.673 --> 04:18.549
TAKE DETECTIVE SANCHEZ
WITH YOU.

04:19.634 --> 04:20.802
CHIEF.

04:19.634 --> 04:20.802
YES?

04:20.885 --> 04:23.429
I GOT WATER HERE.
I GOT WATER HERE!

04:23.513 --> 04:25.056
LET ME CALL YOU
RIGHT BACK.

04:25.139 --> 04:27.850
WESLEY! WESLEY,
WHAT ARE YOU DOING IN THERE?!

04:27.934 --> 04:29.477
OPEN THE DOOR
THIS INSTANT!

04:29.560 --> 04:31.354
[ GLASS SHATTERS ]

04:29.560 --> 04:31.354
HE'S BREAKING
THE WINDOW.

04:31.437 --> 04:33.022
CLAY, I'M PULLING OFF
THE HIGHWAY.

04:33.106 --> 04:36.192
PULL OFF THE FIRST STREET
AND PARK AS QUICK AS YOU CAN.

04:36.275 --> 04:37.318
OKAY.

04:39.862 --> 04:44.158
SON! IF YOU HURT MY R.V.,
I MAY JUST HAVE TO KILL YOU!

04:44.242 --> 04:45.618
DADDY!
DADDY, PLEASE.

04:45.702 --> 04:47.787
BRENDA LEIGH, NO.
I JUST REPLACED THAT DOOR.

04:47.870 --> 04:49.205
YOU CAN'T KICK IT IN.

04:49.288 --> 04:51.290
I-I'LL UNLOCK IT.
LET ME GO GET THE KEY.

04:51.374 --> 04:53.209
WHY DON'T WE JUST
SHOOT THE BASTARD?

04:53.293 --> 04:55.628
WESLEY REED,
OPEN THIS DOOR THIS INSTANT!

04:55.712 --> 04:57.338
[ RUSTLING ]

04:55.712 --> 04:57.338
HE'S GOING
OUT THE WINDOW, CHIEF.

04:57.422 --> 04:58.965
HE'S GOING
OUT THAT WINDOW.

05:06.180 --> 05:08.099
[ TIRES SCREECH ]

05:08.182 --> 05:09.225
UGH!

05:12.645 --> 05:14.772
GET OFF ME!
GET OFF ME!

05:14.856 --> 05:15.940
WESLEY!

05:17.150 --> 05:18.443
[ SIGHS ]

05:22.155 --> 05:25.033
[ TAPE RIPPING ]

05:27.952 --> 05:30.413
SO, CLAY,
WHAT'S THE GOOD NEWS?

05:30.496 --> 05:32.331
WELL,
YOUR LITTLE FRIEND THERE

05:32.415 --> 05:35.251
NOT ONLY SNAPPED OFF
THE FOOT PADDLE,

05:35.334 --> 05:37.545
HE ALSO STUFFED
HIS SHIRT --

05:35.334 --> 05:37.545
<i>MY</i> SHIRT.

05:37.628 --> 05:39.547
WHOEVER'S SHIRT --
SO FAR DOWN THE TOILET

05:39.630 --> 05:42.884
THAT I HAVE TO HAVE
MY DUMP VALVES SNAKED.

05:42.967 --> 05:45.970
I'M CALLING A PLUMBER
AND HAVE HIM MEET US

05:46.054 --> 05:48.681
AT THE FIRST R.V. MOTEL
WE COME TO.

05:48.765 --> 05:50.600
I'M SO SORRY. I'LL PAY
FOR EVERYTHING, I PROMISE.

05:50.683 --> 05:52.060
YOU BET YOU WILL.

05:52.143 --> 05:55.605
IN THE MEANTIME,
THAT HEAD IS OFF LIMITS.

05:55.688 --> 05:56.689
DAMN IT!

05:56.773 --> 05:57.940
COME ON, EVERYBODY.
GET ON.

05:58.024 --> 05:59.859
WAIT --
CLAY, ARE YOU TELLING ME

05:59.942 --> 06:02.028
WE'RE GONNA GO CROSS-COUNTRY
WITH NO WORKING TOILET?

06:02.111 --> 06:04.614
THE PIONEERS
WHO SETTLED THIS COUNTRY

06:04.697 --> 06:06.449
DIDN'T HAVE
WORKING TOILETS,

06:06.532 --> 06:08.868
AND THEY DIDN'T HAVE
HUNDREDS OF CLEAN REST STOPS

06:08.951 --> 06:10.369
ALL ALONG THE HIGHWAY.

06:10.453 --> 06:11.913
WE'LL MANAGE,
LIEUTENANT.

06:11.996 --> 06:12.955
YES, MA'AM.

06:13.039 --> 06:14.123
COME ON.

06:14.207 --> 06:15.583
OW!

06:15.666 --> 06:18.544
WILL YOU KNOCK IT OFF?!
WHAT DO YOU THINK YOU'RE DOING?

06:18.628 --> 06:20.254
FRITZ, WOULD YOU LIKE
TO GIVE ME A HAND, PLEASE?

06:20.338 --> 06:22.465
I'M NOT GETTING BACK
ON THAT THING.

06:22.548 --> 06:23.382
OH, YEAH?

06:23.466 --> 06:24.634
HEY, HELP! HELP!

06:24.717 --> 06:27.387
THESE PEOPLE ARE TRYING
TO KIDNAP ME!

06:27.470 --> 06:28.554
SHUT UP!

06:28.638 --> 06:31.265
CALL THE POLICE!
HELP!

06:31.349 --> 06:35.019
FBI, LADIES AND GENTLEMEN. FBI.
SORRY FOR THE INTERRUPTION.

06:35.103 --> 06:37.396
LISTEN TO ME, YOU DELINQUENT --
I WANT YOU TO CALM DOWN,

06:37.480 --> 06:40.316
GET OUT FROM UNDER THIS TABLE,
AND GET ON THAT R.V. NOW!

06:40.399 --> 06:41.776
NOT UNTIL
I TALK TO MY BROTHER.

06:41.859 --> 06:43.736
I'M AFRAID
THAT'S NOT POSSIBLE, WESLEY.

06:43.820 --> 06:45.530
WHY NOT?
WHY CAN'T I SPEAK TO HIM?

06:45.613 --> 06:47.073
I DIDN'T WANT TO HAVE TO
TELL YOU THIS,

06:47.156 --> 06:49.158
BUT ON THE DAY
THAT YOU LEFT LOS ANGELES,

06:49.242 --> 06:51.577
UNIDENTIFIED ASSAILANTS
BROKE INTO THE APARTMENT

06:51.661 --> 06:53.955
THAT YOU SHARE WITH GRADY
AND ATTACKED HIM.

06:55.289 --> 06:56.874
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

06:56.958 --> 06:59.669
BY THE TIME RESPONDING OFFICERS
ARRIVED ON THE SCENE,

06:59.752 --> 07:01.170
GRADY, WHO HAD BEEN SHOT

07:01.254 --> 07:04.173
SEVERAL TIMES AT CLOSE RANGE
WITH AN AUTOMATIC WEAPON,

07:04.257 --> 07:06.300
COULD NOT BE RESUSCITATED.

07:14.600 --> 07:15.685
YOU'RE LYING.

07:15.768 --> 07:17.603
I WISH I WERE.

07:19.272 --> 07:21.524
WHERE IS HE?
WHERE IS HE RIGHT NOW?

07:23.943 --> 07:25.319
HE'S AT THE L.A. MORGUE,

07:25.403 --> 07:28.030
PENDING NOTIFICATION
OF NEXT OF KIN FOR FUNERAL --

07:28.114 --> 07:30.700
<i>I'M</i> HIS NEXT OF KIN!
<i>I</i> AM!

07:30.783 --> 07:33.703
I'M HIS...NEXT OF KIN.

07:33.786 --> 07:35.621
I'M SORRY ABOUT THIS,
WESLEY.

07:35.705 --> 07:37.999
I REALLY AM.

07:40.293 --> 07:41.919
NO! NO!

07:42.003 --> 07:44.130
[ GRUNTING ]

07:51.804 --> 07:53.431
[ SOBBING ]

07:53.514 --> 07:55.308
WESLEY...

07:55.391 --> 07:58.936
DON'T THINK ABOUT ANYTHING ELSE
FOR A SECOND.

07:59.020 --> 08:00.688
JUST GIVE ME YOUR HAND.

08:14.619 --> 08:15.703
COME ON.

08:35.348 --> 08:36.641
CHIEF...

08:36.724 --> 08:39.310
CHIEF, I-I DON'T KNOW
IF THAT WAS SUCH A GOOD IDEA.

08:39.393 --> 08:41.312
IF IT GETS HIM TO TALK,

08:41.395 --> 08:43.439
IT'S AN<i> EXCELLENT</i> IDEA,
LIEUTENANT.

08:43.522 --> 08:45.691
BEFORE YOU GET BACK ON
THE R.V., I'D LIKE YOU
TO CALL LIEUTENANT TAO.

08:45.775 --> 08:47.735
HAVE HIM GO BACK
TO WESLEY'S APARTMENT

08:47.818 --> 08:50.571
AND FAKE A CRIME SCENE
DEPICTING GRADY'S MURDER.

08:50.655 --> 08:52.657
THANK YOU.

08:57.328 --> 08:58.955
WHERE THE HELL
IS EVERYBODY?

08:59.038 --> 09:01.624
UH...GOOD EVENING,
CHIEF POPE.

09:01.707 --> 09:04.669
WHY ARE CHIEF JOHNSON
AND FLYNN AND PROVENZA
NOT BACK WITH OUR SUSPECT?

09:04.752 --> 09:07.296
UH, THE D.A. WOULDN'T ALLOW
PAYMENT ON AN EXTRADITION ORDER,

09:07.380 --> 09:09.799
BASED ON WESLEY'S ABSENCE
FROM A DIVERSION PROGRAM.

09:09.882 --> 09:13.594
SO I FAXED CHIEF JOHNSON
A WAIVER

09:13.678 --> 09:16.180
WHICH, IF THE SUSPECT SIGNS IT,
IT WILL ALLOW US TO --

09:16.264 --> 09:19.058
SHE EXPECTS WESLEY REED
TO REMAND HIMSELF

09:19.141 --> 09:20.601
INTO L.A.P.D. CUSTODY

09:20.685 --> 09:22.979
WHILE WE'RE INVESTIGATING HIM
FOR FELONY MURDER?

09:23.062 --> 09:25.856
AND SHE NEEDS FLYNN
AND PROVENZA TO HELP
HER ACCOMPLISH THAT?

09:25.940 --> 09:28.317
UM, THERE -- YOU KNOW,
THERE WAS AN AIRPORT PROBLEM,

09:28.401 --> 09:29.777
AND, UNFORTUNATELY --

09:29.860 --> 09:30.820
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.

09:30.903 --> 09:32.321
ARE YOU TELLING ME

09:32.405 --> 09:35.366
THEY ARE<i> DRIVING</i> THE SUSPECT
HERE FROM ATLANTA?

09:35.449 --> 09:38.411
YOU KNOW, THEY'RE ALMOST HERE --
MAKING REALLY GOOD TIME.

09:38.494 --> 09:39.996
THEY'RE IN WILLCOX,
ARIZONA.

09:40.079 --> 09:42.164
WITHOUT A WARRANT?

09:42.248 --> 09:44.458
GET CHIEF JOHNSON
ON THE PHONE -- NOW.

09:45.584 --> 09:47.211
[ SIGHS ]

09:47.295 --> 09:51.549
WESLEY, YOU HAVEN'T EATEN
SINCE DAY BEFORE YESTERDAY.

09:52.508 --> 09:53.634
OKAY.

09:53.718 --> 09:55.886
I'VE GOT LIEUTENANTS
FLYNN AND PROVENZA

09:55.970 --> 09:59.682
ALL SQUARED AWAY IN THE MOTEL,
AND HERE'S THE RECEIPT.

09:59.765 --> 10:01.559
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]
OH, GREAT.

10:01.642 --> 10:03.519
IF YOU DON'T WANT
THE FRIED CHICKEN,

10:03.602 --> 10:05.813
I'LL BET WE COULD GET YOU
A HAMBURGER SOMEWHERE.

10:05.896 --> 10:07.189
HELLO?

10:07.273 --> 10:08.691
I'M SORRY, CHIEF.
IT'S HER VOICE MAIL.

10:08.774 --> 10:10.067
I'LL JUST LEAVE HER
A MESSAGE.

10:10.151 --> 10:11.360
PERHAPS SHE ALREADY

10:10.151 --> 10:11.360
RECEIVED THE WAIVER

10:11.444 --> 10:12.737
AND SHE'S GONNA CALL
TO CONFIRM.

10:12.820 --> 10:15.031
I've got the waiver
in my hand.

10:15.114 --> 10:17.700
I DON'T KNOW HOW I'M EVER
GONNA GET WESLEY TO SIGN IT
WHEN HE WON'T EVEN TALK TO ME.

10:17.783 --> 10:19.535
I DO NOT KNOW.

10:19.618 --> 10:20.953
[ SIGHS ]

10:21.037 --> 10:23.205
ARE YOU STANDING
RIGHT NEXT TO POPE?

10:23.289 --> 10:24.749
UH, HELLO, CHIEF.

10:24.832 --> 10:25.958
THIS IS LIEUTENANT TAO,

10:26.042 --> 10:27.668
AND CHIEF POPE
WOULD LIKE ME TO TELL YOU --

10:27.752 --> 10:30.129
GIVE ME THE PHONE.

10:27.752 --> 10:30.129
UH, CHIEF POPE
WILL TELL YOU HIMSELF.

10:30.212 --> 10:32.298
FREEZE!
[ PLATES CLATTERING ]

10:32.381 --> 10:35.426
[ SILVERWARE CLANKS ]

10:35.509 --> 10:37.386
CHIEF JOHNSON, WHEN I PUT YOU
IN CHARGE OF THIS INVESTIGATION,

10:37.470 --> 10:39.889
IT WAS TO STOP A GANG
THAT USES AUTOMATIC WEAPONS

10:39.972 --> 10:41.515
FROM STRIKING
ANOTHER ARMORED CAR

10:41.599 --> 10:44.393
AND KILLING MORE PEOPLE
<i>HERE</i> IN L.A.

10:44.477 --> 10:45.770
IF YOU'RE NOT BACK HERE
BY TOMORROW AFTERNOON,

10:45.853 --> 10:47.521
Taylor is taking over
the case again.

10:47.605 --> 10:50.149
And you better have
a-a warrant or extradition
papers for Wesley,

10:50.232 --> 10:52.401
BECAUSE I DON'T WANT HIM
GETTING OFF ON MURDER CHARGES

10:52.485 --> 10:54.570
BECAUSE YOU DON'T HAVE
YOUR PAPERWORK IN ORDER.

10:54.653 --> 10:55.988
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

10:56.072 --> 10:57.782
UNFREEZE.

11:02.745 --> 11:05.164
LOOK, DADDY, WE'RE GONNA
HAVE TO GET BACK TO LOS ANGELES

11:05.247 --> 11:06.916
BY LATE
TOMORROW AFTERNOON.

11:06.999 --> 11:09.126
THAT MEANS WE'RE ALL
GONNA HAVE TO LEAVE
REALLY, REALLY EARLY.

11:09.210 --> 11:10.669
I'M -- I'M SO SORRY.

11:10.753 --> 11:13.464
YOU KNOW, IF YOU DON'T MIND ME
STICKING MY NOSE IN,

11:13.547 --> 11:15.091
I'VE BEEN THINKING ABOUT

11:15.174 --> 11:17.718
THE PROBLEM YOU AND YOUR MOTHER
HAVE BEEN HAVING,

11:17.802 --> 11:22.681
AND I'VE COME UP WITH
A TWO-BIRD, ONE-STONE SOLUTION.

11:24.350 --> 11:25.518
OVER 21?

11:28.354 --> 11:31.107
WESLEY,
YOU KNOW WHAT?

11:31.190 --> 11:35.277
I THINK YOU'RE STILL
IN A LITTLE BIT OF SHOCK,

11:35.361 --> 11:39.073
[ GLASSES CLINKING ]

11:35.361 --> 11:39.073
AND WHAT YOU MAY NEED
TO GET YOUR APPETITE BACK

11:39.156 --> 11:42.576
IS A GOOD, STIFF DRINK...

11:42.660 --> 11:44.203
OR TWO.

11:44.286 --> 11:47.039
DO YOU TAKE IT ON THE ROCKS
OR STRAIGHT UP, SON?

11:47.123 --> 11:48.332
YOU GOT ANY COKE?

11:48.416 --> 11:50.709
COKE?
SON, THAT'S PREMIUM BOURBON.

11:50.793 --> 11:52.420
YOU DON'T PUT SODA
IN THAT.

11:52.503 --> 11:54.630
I DRINK IT WITH COKE.

11:54.713 --> 11:55.965
DADDY, GET THE COKE.

11:56.048 --> 11:57.591
[ SIGHS ]

11:58.717 --> 12:01.095
DOESN'T SEEM RIGHT,
THOUGH.

12:01.178 --> 12:03.639
YOU KNOW, WESLEY HAS
A DRUG AND ALCOHOL PROBLEM.

12:03.722 --> 12:06.142
AND HIS FRIENDS ARE
KILLING PEOPLE WITH UZIS.

12:06.225 --> 12:08.227
WOULD YOU RATHER SEE
WESLEY HUNG OVER

12:08.310 --> 12:10.604
OR MORE DEAD GUARDS
ON THE NEWS?

12:10.688 --> 12:12.314
PICK YOUR POISON.

12:12.398 --> 12:16.861
WELL, THE KID'S GOING INTO
LIFETIME REHAB, ANYWAY.

12:22.700 --> 12:23.868
THANKS.

12:28.747 --> 12:31.000
[ GAGS ]

12:34.587 --> 12:36.338
SECOND DRINK COMES

12:36.422 --> 12:39.258
WHEN YOUR DINNER PLATE
IS HALF EMPTY.

12:47.099 --> 12:48.767
SO, YOU TOLD US
A FEW DAYS AGO

12:48.851 --> 12:51.353
THAT YOUR BROTHER'S FRIEND R.J.
WAS IRRITATED

12:51.437 --> 12:53.522
WHEN WESLEY GOT HIRED
BY TAS, RIGHT?

12:53.606 --> 12:56.025
Y-YEAH. UH...
HE DIDN'T THINK IT WAS FAIR.

12:56.108 --> 13:00.112
SO I WENT THROUGH ALL THE
EMPLOYMENT APPLICATIONS TO TAS

13:00.196 --> 13:03.365
FROM THE SAME TIME
YOUR BROTHER WAS HIRED,

13:03.449 --> 13:06.494
AND I FOUND A GUY
NAMED RANDALL JACKSON GIBSON.

13:06.577 --> 13:08.954
NOW,
TAS TURNED RANDALL DOWN

13:09.038 --> 13:11.290
AFTER SPEAKING
WITH A PREVIOUS EMPLOYER --

13:11.373 --> 13:12.791
THE OWNER
OF A USED-CAR DEALERSHIP --

13:12.875 --> 13:15.127
AND HE SAID THAT WHILE
RANDALL WAS WORKING FOR HIM,

13:15.211 --> 13:16.879
SEVERAL OF HIS VEHICLES
WENT MISSING,

13:16.962 --> 13:19.089
INCLUDING AN ASTRO VAN.

13:19.173 --> 13:22.426
THAT'S ONE OF THE GETAWAY
VEHICLES THE GANG WHO SHOT
AT YOUR BROTHER USES.

13:22.510 --> 13:25.221
SO YOU GOT TO LOOK
AT THESE PHOTOS.

13:25.304 --> 13:26.388
OKAY?

13:26.472 --> 13:28.974
IF YOU COULD IDENTIFY R.J.
FOR US --

13:29.058 --> 13:30.476
W-WHAT ABOUT THUMPS?

13:30.559 --> 13:32.770
THEY ROLL TOGETHER --
R.J. AND THUMPS.

13:32.853 --> 13:34.480
LOOK, GRADY, GRADY.

13:34.563 --> 13:37.525
THESE GUYS ARE
GOING TO KILL YOUR BROTHER.

13:37.608 --> 13:39.401
AND IF WE LET YOU GO,
GUESS WHAT.

13:39.485 --> 13:40.444
THEY'RE GONNA BE
WAITING FOR YOU.

13:40.528 --> 13:41.862
SO HERE'S THE DEAL --

13:41.946 --> 13:44.823
I GOT A BUNCH OF PHOTOS HERE,
AND ONE OF THESE IS R.J.

13:44.907 --> 13:47.493
SO YOU NEED TO
PICK HIM OUT RIGHT NOW!

13:47.576 --> 13:49.870
OR I AM GOING TO DRIVE YOU
TO FAMILY SERVICES,

13:49.954 --> 13:53.666
WHERE THEY WILL PLACE YOU
IN FOSTER CARE -- AND BANG!

13:53.749 --> 13:56.794
WE'LL SEND FLOWERS
TO YOUR FUNERAL.

13:56.877 --> 14:00.756
YOU -- YOU SAID -- YOU SAID
I WAS A MATERIAL WITNESS.

14:00.839 --> 14:02.758
YOU SAID
THAT I HAD TO BE PROTECTED.

14:02.841 --> 14:05.094
YEAH, WELL,
YOU'RE NOT A WITNESS

14:05.177 --> 14:06.804
IF YOU DID NOT
<i>SEE</i> ANYTHING!

14:06.887 --> 14:09.139
SO IF YOU CANNOT
IDENTIFY R.J.,

14:09.223 --> 14:11.350
WE GOT NO REASON
TO PROTECT YOU!

14:15.854 --> 14:18.732
YOU SWEAR
THIS HELPS MY BROTHER?

14:18.816 --> 14:20.484
ON YOUR HONOR?

14:24.071 --> 14:25.823
ON MY HONOR.

14:29.702 --> 14:30.452
4.

14:30.536 --> 14:32.288
NOW,
ARE YOU SURE?

14:32.371 --> 14:33.998
IT'S 4.

14:36.166 --> 14:37.960
[ CAMERA CLICKS ]

14:36.166 --> 14:37.960
WE WENT
TO THIS GUY'S APARTMENT.

14:38.043 --> 14:39.712
HE WASN'T THERE --
NO FORWARDING ADDRESS.

14:39.795 --> 14:42.673
SO I'VE PICKED HIM OUT,
AND YOU CAN'T EVEN FIND HIM?

14:42.756 --> 14:45.092
TRUST ME --
I'LL FIND HIM.

14:45.175 --> 14:46.635
ON MY HONOR.

14:53.392 --> 14:56.020
Wesley:
[ Slurred ] HEY.

14:56.103 --> 14:58.689
HOW ABOUT A ROADIE?

14:58.772 --> 15:01.066
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

15:01.150 --> 15:03.652
HEY. BRENDA?

15:03.736 --> 15:05.613
ON ONE CONDITION.

15:05.696 --> 15:09.408
I NEED TO GET
SOME FRESH AIR.

15:15.497 --> 15:17.166
[ Laughing ]
WHAT'S<i> HIS</i> PROBLEM?

15:17.249 --> 15:19.710
JUST A LITTLE TIRED,
I GUESS.

15:19.793 --> 15:21.545
SO, YOU WANT THAT DRINK
OR NOT?

15:21.629 --> 15:22.755
YEAH.

15:24.006 --> 15:26.425
I NEED YOU TO LOOK
AT A PICTURE FIRST.

15:26.508 --> 15:27.551
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

15:27.635 --> 15:30.012
A WITNESS
IDENTIFIED THIS MAN

15:30.095 --> 15:32.222
AS ONE OF THE TWO PEOPLE
FLEEING FROM YOUR APARTMENT

15:32.306 --> 15:35.517
ON THE NIGHT
THAT GRADY WAS MURDERED.

15:35.601 --> 15:38.228
RANDALL JACKSON GIBSON.

15:42.483 --> 15:44.985
WESLEY,
I NEED YOU TO HELP ME

15:45.069 --> 15:47.446
FIND THE GUYS
WHO MURDERED YOUR BROTHER.

15:47.529 --> 15:50.074
AND YOU<i> CAN</i> HELP ME.

15:50.157 --> 15:51.450
I KNOW IT.

15:52.618 --> 15:54.870
NO ONE WAS
SUPPOSED TO GET HURT.

15:54.953 --> 15:57.164
THEY -- THEY PROMISED.

15:57.247 --> 15:59.458
THEY WERE JUST --

15:59.541 --> 16:02.461
JUST SUPPOSED TO SHOOT
ACROSS MY WINDSHIELD.

16:02.544 --> 16:06.882
BUT THEN
I...SAW ARNIE GET HIT.

16:06.965 --> 16:10.552
AND I SAW HIM FALL,
AND I, UH...

16:15.599 --> 16:17.768
YOU GOT OUT OF THE CAR.

16:17.851 --> 16:19.395
YOU BROKE WITH THE PLAN.

16:19.478 --> 16:22.523
I YELLED AT THEM
TO STOP IT.

16:22.606 --> 16:24.608
AND THEN
THEY FIRED AT<i> ME.</i>

16:24.692 --> 16:27.945
I-I DIDN'T KNOW
WHAT TO DO.

16:28.028 --> 16:31.240
[ Voice breaking ]
I WAS SO...SCARED

16:31.323 --> 16:34.410
THAT I LEFT GRADY BEHIND.

16:34.493 --> 16:38.997
I LEFT HIM BEHIND 'CAUSE
I WAS TOO SCARED TO GO HOME.

16:39.081 --> 16:41.250
I RAN OUT
ON MY LITTLE BROTHER.

16:41.333 --> 16:43.293
[ Crying ]
I RAN OUT ON HIM.

16:43.377 --> 16:45.504
I RAN OUT ON HIM.

16:48.465 --> 16:50.092
[ SNIFFLES ]

16:53.929 --> 16:56.265
[ PLASTIC CRINKLING ]

16:56.348 --> 16:58.016
SO...

16:58.100 --> 17:00.436
RANDALL JACKSON
IS YOUR FRIEND.

17:01.687 --> 17:03.731
AND --
AND THE OTHER GUY?

17:03.814 --> 17:05.649
[ SNIFFLES ]

17:08.736 --> 17:09.862
THUMPS.

17:11.071 --> 17:12.448
JIMMY GRISSOM.

17:12.531 --> 17:14.908
HE AND R.J.
ARE METH HEADS.

17:14.992 --> 17:17.411
I STOPPED USING WHEN --
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

17:17.494 --> 17:19.830
...WHEN I GOT GRADY.

17:19.913 --> 17:22.666
I WENT TO ATLANTA
AND TOOK HIM TO L.A.

17:22.750 --> 17:24.960
'CAUSE
MY STUPID GRANDMOTHER...

17:28.547 --> 17:30.841
YOU KNOW
HOW LUCKY YOU ARE?

17:30.924 --> 17:32.634
HUH?

17:32.718 --> 17:34.344
DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA?

17:34.428 --> 17:35.554
LUCKY?

17:35.637 --> 17:37.681
YOU THINK EVERYONE
GROWS UP IN A FAMILY

17:37.765 --> 17:41.018
WITH A MOM AND A DAD
WHO CAN TAKE CARE OF 'EM?

17:41.101 --> 17:42.603
'CAUSE THEY DON'T.

17:42.686 --> 17:46.648
WELL, MY DADDY -- HE DROPPED
ME AND GRADY OFF AT GRAN'S

17:46.732 --> 17:50.486
WHEN I WAS 9,
AND HE NEVER CAME BACK.

17:50.569 --> 17:54.656
AND MY MOTHER WAS AN ADDICT,
WHO FINALLY O.D.'d LAST YEAR.

17:54.740 --> 17:56.283
SO I TOOK GRADY
FROM GRAN

17:56.366 --> 17:58.952
BECAUSE SOMEONE
HAD TO LOOK AFTER HIM.

18:03.582 --> 18:06.376
WHY DID THEY HAVE TO
HURT HIM? WHY?

18:06.460 --> 18:08.879
MAYBE THEY WERE MAD AT YOU
'CAUSE YOU RAN AWAY.

18:08.962 --> 18:11.089
Y'ALL WERE
SUPPOSED TO BE PARTNERS.

18:11.173 --> 18:13.300
YOU EVEN JOINED TAS

18:13.383 --> 18:16.011
SO YOU COULD FIND OUT
WHERE THE BIG HAULS WERE.

18:16.095 --> 18:17.554
ISN'T THAT RIGHT?

18:19.014 --> 18:20.140
YOU KNOW WHAT?

18:20.224 --> 18:21.975
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

18:22.059 --> 18:23.560
I LIKED IT THERE.

18:25.604 --> 18:26.897
ARNIE --

18:26.980 --> 18:28.857
[ INHALES,
EXHALES DEEPLY ]

18:28.941 --> 18:30.359
HE WAS MY FRIEND.

18:30.442 --> 18:33.654
HE USED TO HAVE US OVER
FOR DINNER.

18:33.737 --> 18:36.281
THEN, UM...

18:36.365 --> 18:40.744
HAYES TOOK ME AND GRADY
TO A PROFESSIONAL BASEBALL GAME.

18:40.828 --> 18:42.120
DODGERS.

18:42.204 --> 18:43.914
AND THEY HAD FIREWORKS.

18:43.997 --> 18:47.376
AND GRADY SAID
IT WAS THE BEST NIGHT OF...

18:54.299 --> 18:56.802
WHERE ARE R.J...

18:56.885 --> 18:58.512
AND THUMPS?

18:59.930 --> 19:01.807
I DON'T KNOW.

19:01.890 --> 19:03.517
YOU WERE IN CONTACT
WITH THEM.

19:03.600 --> 19:05.978
NOT ONCE I GOT THE JOB
WITH TAS.

19:07.521 --> 19:08.897
WELL, UH...

19:08.981 --> 19:11.233
THEY USED TO SEND ME --
WHAT IS IT? --

19:11.316 --> 19:14.027
A DISPOSABLE PHONE IN THE MAIL
AND CALL ME,

19:14.111 --> 19:15.529
AND I GAVE THEM
ROUTE INFORMATION.

19:15.612 --> 19:17.948
WHEN I WAS DONE WITH IT,
I THREW THE PHONE AWAY.

19:20.075 --> 19:22.995
WE WEREN'T EVEN SUPPOSED TO
MEET UP TILL OUR NEXT JOB.

19:23.078 --> 19:24.580
THERE'S GONNA BE
ANOTHER ROBBERY?

19:24.663 --> 19:25.956
CHRISTMAS EVE.

19:26.039 --> 19:27.374
WHERE?

19:30.502 --> 19:32.129
I COULD FIND OUT WHERE.

19:32.212 --> 19:33.922
I KNOW
R.J.'s GIRLFRIEND --

19:34.006 --> 19:35.591
NOT HER NAME,
BUT HER FACE.

19:35.674 --> 19:39.052
AND I KNOW
WHERE SHE HANGS OUT.

19:40.304 --> 19:41.638
ALL RIGHT, WESLEY.

19:41.722 --> 19:45.392
IN ORDER TO SET UP A DEAL
FOR YOU WITH THE D.A.,

19:45.475 --> 19:49.813
I'M GONNA NEED YOU TO SIGN
THIS EXTRADITION WAIVER.

19:49.897 --> 19:52.691
AND THEN YOU CAN HELP US
FIND R.J. AND THUMPS,

19:52.774 --> 19:55.611
AND MAYBE SOME GOOD
WILL COME OUT OF ALL THIS.

19:55.694 --> 19:57.279
YEAH.

19:57.362 --> 20:00.240
[ GRUNTS, SNIFFLES ]

20:00.324 --> 20:02.409
LIKE MAYBE THEY GET
THEIR HEADS BLOWN OFF.

20:12.711 --> 20:14.922
THANK YOU, WESLEY.

20:15.005 --> 20:17.591
YOU KNOW,
WHEN ALL THIS IS OVER --

20:17.674 --> 20:19.051
IT'S OVER ALREADY,
BRENDA.

20:19.134 --> 20:22.679
IT WAS OVER
THE DAY BEFORE YESTERDAY.

20:32.606 --> 20:33.690
NO, THANKS.

20:33.774 --> 20:35.150
[ SNIFFLES ]

20:35.233 --> 20:36.902
IT'S NOT HELPING ANYMORE.

20:53.085 --> 20:55.504
WELCOME BACK, CHIEF.
HEY, CHIEF.

20:55.587 --> 20:56.880
DETECTIVE, LIEUTENANT.

20:56.964 --> 20:58.840
ARE YOUR PARENTS
WITH YOU?

20:58.924 --> 21:01.718
UH, THEY ARE JUST ABOUT
TO PARK THE R.V.

21:01.802 --> 21:03.595
IN FRONT OF MY HOUSE
IN ABOUT 25 MINUTES.

21:03.679 --> 21:04.513
WHAT'S HAPPENING HERE?

21:04.596 --> 21:05.847
ROBBERY/HOMICIDE DIVISION

21:05.931 --> 21:07.849
IS STILL STAKING OUT
LIKELY TARGET BANKS

21:07.933 --> 21:09.851
BASED ON
WESLEY'S SCHEDULED ROUTE.

21:09.935 --> 21:12.354
AND WE CUED UP THE CRIME-SCENE
VIDEO YOU ASKED FOR.

21:12.437 --> 21:14.815
WONDERFUL.
THANK YOU.

21:14.898 --> 21:16.525
Flynn: OKAY, WESLEY.

21:16.608 --> 21:17.734
COME ON.

21:17.818 --> 21:20.988
THERE'S SOMETHING
YOU NEED TO SEE.

21:21.071 --> 21:22.781
DO YOU HAVE A DEPUTY D.A.
COMING IN

21:22.864 --> 21:24.116
AND A LAWYER FOR WESLEY?

21:24.199 --> 21:25.909
THEY'RE IN AN INTERVIEW ROOM
TOGETHER,

21:25.993 --> 21:28.954
AND CHIEF POPE WANTS
TO SEE YOU UPSTAIRS
AS SOON AS YOU'RE DONE.

21:29.037 --> 21:30.080
OKAY.

21:30.163 --> 21:31.206
CHIEF.

21:31.289 --> 21:32.874
YOU GOT
THE BOY'S CONFESSION.

21:32.958 --> 21:35.585
I-I THINK HE WOULD BE
EVEN MORE COOPERATIVE

21:35.669 --> 21:38.380
IF HE KNEW THAT
HIS LITTLE BROTHER WAS ALIVE.

21:38.463 --> 21:40.215
THAT'S A GAMBLE,
LIEUTENANT.

21:45.178 --> 21:46.471
OKAY, WESLEY.

21:46.555 --> 21:48.473
YOU REALLY
WANT TO SEE THIS?

21:52.894 --> 21:54.730
OKAY, BUZZ.

21:58.817 --> 22:01.528
<i>BUZZ. IN HERE.</i>

22:05.991 --> 22:08.201
Buzz:<i> YOU HAVE TO IDENTIFY</i>
<i>YOURSELF FOR THE COURT.</i>

22:08.285 --> 22:09.703
<i>OH, SORRY. HELLO.</i>

22:09.786 --> 22:11.955
<i>LIEUTENANT MICHAEL TAO,</i>
<i>PRIORITY HOMICIDE.</i>

22:12.039 --> 22:13.707
<i>WE BELIEVE</i>
<i>THE STRUGGLE BEGAN IN HERE</i>

22:13.790 --> 22:15.917
<i>WHEN THE ASSAILANTS</i>
<i>DISCOVERED OUR VICTIM</i>

22:16.001 --> 22:17.753
<i>HIDING UNDERNEATH THIS BED.</i>

22:17.836 --> 22:21.298
<i>WE ALSO FEEL THAT WHEN</i>
<i>THE INFORMATION WAS EXTRACTED,</i>

22:21.381 --> 22:25.594
<i>SOMEONE OR SOMEBODY</i>
<i>TOOK SOMETHING OUT OF HERE.</i>

22:25.677 --> 22:26.928
<i>GO TO JULIO --</i>

22:27.012 --> 22:29.514
<i>UH, DETECTIVE SANCHEZ.</i>

22:29.598 --> 22:31.808
Sanchez:
<i>DETECTIVE JULIO SANCHEZ.</i>

22:31.892 --> 22:33.560
<i>WE THINK THIS BLOOD CAME</i>
<i>FROM OUR VICTIM'S SCALP</i>

22:33.643 --> 22:35.270
<i>WHEN HIS HEAD</i>
<i>STRUCK THE WALL HERE.</i>

22:35.353 --> 22:37.939
<i>THE VICTIM SUFFERED</i>
<i>MULTIPLE GUNSHOT WOUNDS</i>

22:38.023 --> 22:40.150
<i>HERE, HERE, AND HERE.</i>

22:40.233 --> 22:42.778
<i>CONTUSIONS, LACERATIONS,</i>
<i>AND ABRASIONS.</i>

22:42.861 --> 22:45.989
<i>THE VICTIM WAS FOUND</i>
<i>DUCT-TAPED TO THIS CHAIR.</i>

22:48.992 --> 22:51.119
<i>GET THAT SIDE.</i>

22:52.370 --> 22:54.873
<i>FOR NOW, THAT'S IT, BUZZ.</i>
<i>THANKS.</i>

22:58.210 --> 22:59.920
[ TV SHUTS OFF ]

23:04.007 --> 23:05.967
WHAT DO YOU
WANT ME TO DO?

23:06.051 --> 23:08.136
LAST NIGHT, WESLEY REED
SIGNED A WAIVER

23:08.220 --> 23:09.888
ALLOWING US
TO TRANSFER HIM

23:09.971 --> 23:12.015
FROM GEORGIA
TO THE CUSTODY OF THE L.A.P.D.

23:12.099 --> 23:15.060
HE'S BEEN READ HIS RIGHTS
IN FRONT OF A PUBLIC DEFENDER,

23:15.143 --> 23:16.394
REPEATED HIS CONFESSION,

23:16.478 --> 23:18.396
AND MADE A DEAL
WITH THE D.A.

23:18.480 --> 23:21.441
TO TURN STATE'S EVIDENCE
AGAINST OUR SHOOTERS.

23:21.525 --> 23:23.360
Provenza:
IN RETURN FOR LENIENCY,

23:23.443 --> 23:25.612
WESLEY'S AGREED
TO WEAR A WIRE AND A CAMERA

23:25.695 --> 23:27.739
AND MAKE AN ATTEMPT
TO LOCATE

23:27.823 --> 23:29.491
RANDALL JACKSON GIBSON,
A.K.A. R.J.,

23:29.574 --> 23:31.118
AND JAMES GRISSOM,
A.K.A. THUMPS,

23:31.201 --> 23:32.994
BEFORE THEIR NEXT ROBBERY,

23:33.078 --> 23:35.539
WHICH HE BELIEVES
WILL HAPPEN SOMETIME TOMORROW.

23:35.622 --> 23:37.165
GREAT WORK.

23:37.249 --> 23:39.167
YOU GOT A CONFESSION, AND NOW
WE HAVE EVERYTHING WE NEED

23:39.251 --> 23:41.920
TO PUT THESE OTHER TWO GUYS AWAY
ONCE WE FIND THEM.

23:42.003 --> 23:45.423
I HAVE S.I.S. UNITS COORDINATING
WITH ROBBERY/HOMICIDE

23:45.507 --> 23:47.008
ALL ALONG WESLEY'S ROUTE.

23:47.092 --> 23:49.970
OF COURSE, THE ARMORED CARS
WON'T HAVE ANY CASH ON THEM,

23:50.053 --> 23:51.346
AND THEY'LL BE COVERED

23:51.429 --> 23:54.182
BY NEARLY AN ENTIRE DIVISION
OF POLICE OFFICERS.

23:54.266 --> 23:57.018
IN ORDER TO ENLIST
HIS COOPERATION, I TOLD WESLEY

23:57.102 --> 23:59.354
THAT R.J. AND THUMPS
MURDERED HIS LITTLE BROTHER.

23:59.437 --> 24:00.647
SO I FEEL RESPONSIBLE
FOR --

24:00.730 --> 24:02.399
SENDING WESLEY
BACK OUT ON THE STREET

24:02.482 --> 24:04.484
IS A CONDITION
OF HIS AGREEMENT WITH THE D.A.,

24:04.568 --> 24:06.236
SO...
IT'S NOT YOUR PROBLEM.

24:06.319 --> 24:08.029
SET UP THE WIRE ON WESLEY,
TURN HIM OVER

24:08.113 --> 24:09.781
TO COMMANDER TAYLOR
AND DETECTIVE ROSS,

24:09.865 --> 24:12.742
AND ENJOY WHAT'S LEFT OF
YOUR HOLIDAY WHILE THEY MOP UP.

24:12.826 --> 24:15.453
AND SO, AFTERWARD,
YOU'LL LET WESLEY AND GRADY

24:15.537 --> 24:18.123
MEET FOR AN HOUR
ON CHRISTMAS DAY?

24:18.206 --> 24:19.708
LOOK,
WESLEY MADE A DEAL.

24:19.791 --> 24:22.085
BUT IF HE HADN'T TURNED
STATE'S EVIDENCE,

24:22.169 --> 24:23.587
HE'D BE LOOKING
AT THE DEATH PENALTY,

24:23.670 --> 24:25.046
WHICH I THINK
HE DESERVES.

24:25.130 --> 24:26.715
PLEASE DON'T TELL ME
YOU'RE FEELING

24:26.798 --> 24:29.426
SOME SORT OF MISPLACED
HOLIDAY COMPASSION HERE,

24:29.509 --> 24:31.386
BECAUSE, TO ME,
THIS KID'S A KILLER.

24:31.469 --> 24:32.929
AND I TREATED HIM
LIKE ONE.

24:33.013 --> 24:35.557
BUT FOR THE SAKE OF
HIS LITTLE BROTHER, I THINK --

24:35.640 --> 24:39.019
I, UH, SEE NO PROBLEM
WITH A CHRISTMAS VISIT, CHIEF.

24:39.102 --> 24:41.313
WELL, IF YOU WANT
TO BRING A TEENAGE BOY

24:41.396 --> 24:44.566
TO COUNTY JAIL
ON CHRISTMAS DAY, OKAY.

24:44.649 --> 24:46.109
THANK YOU, COMMANDER.

24:46.193 --> 24:48.653
W-WAIT A MINUTE, CHIEF.

24:48.737 --> 24:50.530
UH, WE SPENT DAYS
WITH WESLEY.

24:50.614 --> 24:52.616
I MEAN, WE'VE ESTABLISHED
A RELATIONSHIP WITH HIM.

24:52.699 --> 24:55.202
I DON'T THINK IT'S A GOOD IDEA
TO HAND HIM OFF TO A --

24:55.285 --> 24:56.912
EXCUSE ME, LIEUTENANT.
CHIEF POPE IS RIGHT.

24:56.995 --> 24:58.246
THIS IS
A TACTICAL OPERATION NOW,

24:58.330 --> 25:00.207
FOR WHICH S.I.S.
AND ROBBERY/HOMICIDE

25:00.290 --> 25:03.335
ARE MUCH MORE SUITED
THAN WE ARE.

25:03.418 --> 25:06.171
EXCUSE US, GENTLEMEN.

25:06.254 --> 25:07.923
[ DOOR OPENS ]

25:09.507 --> 25:13.511
WELL, THAT WAS...A LOT EASIER
THAN I THOUGHT IT WOULD BE.

25:13.595 --> 25:14.971
[ SCOFFS ] YEAH.

25:15.055 --> 25:16.806
I WONDER WHY.

25:16.890 --> 25:17.974
MM-HMM.

25:35.951 --> 25:37.953
OKAY.

25:38.036 --> 25:39.913
Flynn:<i> THAT WIRE'S</i>
<i>NOT A HOMING DEVICE.</i>

25:39.996 --> 25:42.123
<i>YOU DON'T LET DETECTIVE ROSS</i>
<i>KNOW WHERE YOU ARE,</i>

25:42.207 --> 25:43.750
<i>HE'LL LOSE YOU.</i>

25:43.833 --> 25:45.752
Ross:<i> IF YOU THINK</i>
<i>YOU'RE ABOUT TO GET IN TROUBLE,</i>

25:45.835 --> 25:48.255
<i>JUST TELL ME WHERE YOU ARE --</i>
<i>I'LL COME RUNNING.</i>

25:48.338 --> 25:50.340
OTHERWISE, I'M GONNA TRY TO STAY
ABOUT HALF A MILE AWAY.

25:50.423 --> 25:52.217
WE DON'T WANT TO MAKE
YOUR FRIENDS NERVOUS.

25:52.300 --> 25:53.802
THE VIDEO CAMERA'S
IN THIS BUTTON.

25:53.885 --> 25:55.220
IT DOESN'T BROADCAST LIVE.

25:55.303 --> 25:57.389
WE DOWNLOAD IT
WHEN YOU GIVE IT BACK TO US.

25:57.472 --> 25:59.975
<i>WHICH MEANS I GOT NO PICTURE</i>
<i>OF WHAT'S GOING ON,</i>

26:00.058 --> 26:01.935
<i>SO KEEP TALKING.</i>

26:02.018 --> 26:03.687
LET ME DO
A SOUND CHECK.

26:12.404 --> 26:14.155
<i>WHERE'S BRENDA?</i>

26:14.239 --> 26:16.700
Ross:
<i>SHE'S NOT PARTICIPATING IN THIS</i>
<i>PHASE OF THE INVESTIGATION.</i>

26:16.783 --> 26:18.994
<i>BUT ISN'T SHE EVEN GONNA</i>
<i>COME IN AND SAY GOODBYE?</i>

26:19.077 --> 26:20.704
Flynn:
<i>LOOK, IT DOESN'T MATTER.</i>

26:20.787 --> 26:23.164
<i>YOU'RE ONLY GONNA BE OUT</i>
<i>ON THE STREET UNTIL TOMORROW.</i>

26:23.248 --> 26:26.626
<i>THEN YOU'RE GONNA RETURN HERE</i>
<i>AND TURN YOURSELF IN.</i>

26:26.710 --> 26:27.919
YOU CAN SEE HER THEN.

26:28.003 --> 26:29.421
OH.

26:29.504 --> 26:30.588
OKAY.

26:30.672 --> 26:33.425
WELL, TELL HER
I SAID "SO LONG."

26:33.508 --> 26:35.135
ALL RIGHT.

26:35.218 --> 26:38.263
<i>LET ME GET OUR END OF THINGS.</i>
<i>I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.</i>

26:39.222 --> 26:40.473
[<i> DOOR CLOSES</i> ]

26:40.557 --> 26:42.100
[<i> SNIFFS</i> ]

26:47.355 --> 26:48.356
ANYTHING ELSE?

26:48.440 --> 26:50.150
UH, NO.
THANK YOU.

26:50.233 --> 26:51.609
UH, JUST, UH...

26:51.693 --> 26:53.903
JUST TRY TO MAKE SURE
HE DOESN'T GET HURT.

26:53.987 --> 26:54.863
DO MY BEST.

26:54.946 --> 26:56.656
THANK YOU.

26:58.325 --> 27:01.036
[<i> DOOR OPENS, CLOSES</i> ]

27:05.248 --> 27:07.334
JUST IN CASE
WE MISS EACH OTHER...

27:07.417 --> 27:10.420
MERRY CHRISTMAS,
LIEUTENANT.

27:13.882 --> 27:15.050
FOR REAL.

27:15.133 --> 27:16.968
YEAH?

27:17.052 --> 27:18.386
OKAY.

27:19.137 --> 27:20.388
MERRY CHRISTMAS.

27:20.472 --> 27:21.806
AND REMEMBER THIS,
WESLEY --

27:21.890 --> 27:24.392
<i>YOU RUN OFF,</i>
<i>THIS WHOLE DEAL GOES AWAY,</i>

27:24.476 --> 27:26.436
AND THEN YOU'RE GONNA BE
FACING TWO CHARGES

27:26.519 --> 27:29.230
OF FELONY MURDER
IN THE FIRST DEGREE.

27:29.314 --> 27:30.482
[ GROANS ]

27:30.565 --> 27:32.108
YOU GOT IT?

27:36.946 --> 27:38.865
ALL RIGHT.
LET'S GO.

27:45.997 --> 27:48.583
[<i> DOOR CLOSES</i> ]

27:50.502 --> 27:52.712
WE HAVE THE TRANSMITTERS
EMBEDDED IN HIS SHOES?

27:52.796 --> 27:54.589
YES, BUT I DON'T WANT
TO OVERSELL IT, CHIEF.

27:54.672 --> 27:56.091
WE HAVE
LONGITUDE AND LATITUDE

27:56.174 --> 27:58.009
AND ABOUT A 100-YARD RADIUS
IN WHICH TO TRACK HIM,

27:58.093 --> 28:00.470
BUT PRECISE, IT IS NOT.

28:00.553 --> 28:03.598
WELL, IT'S
IN TAYLOR'S HANDS NOW.

28:03.681 --> 28:05.934
AND IF THE COMMANDER
DROPS THE BALL,

28:06.017 --> 28:08.103
WE'VE GOT ANOTHER CHANCE
TO PICK IT UP.

28:08.186 --> 28:10.230
[ DOOR OPENS ]

28:15.193 --> 28:16.986
[ DOOR OPENS ]

28:17.070 --> 28:18.488
Shh.

28:20.615 --> 28:21.783
[ DOOR CLOSES GENTLY ]

28:21.866 --> 28:23.284
HI, SERGEANT.

28:26.287 --> 28:28.748
UH...
WELCOME BACK, CHIEF.

28:30.083 --> 28:32.293
WHERE IS EVERYBODY?

28:32.377 --> 28:33.545
FRITZ WENT TO BED,

28:33.628 --> 28:36.089
YOUR FATHER'S ASLEEP
IN THE R.V.,

28:36.172 --> 28:40.051
AND SERGEANT GABRIEL
HAD TO WATCH OVER GRADY HERE.

28:40.135 --> 28:44.431
WHO YOUR FATHER AND I
WERE VERY SURPRISED TO MEET.

28:44.514 --> 28:46.850
ANYWAY, I STAYED UP
WITH THE SERGEANT
TO KEEP HIM COMPANY

28:46.933 --> 28:48.143
UNTIL YOU CAME HOME.

28:50.478 --> 28:52.814
UH, I'M GONNA...
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

28:52.897 --> 28:54.482
...STEP OUT ON THE PORCH
FOR A MINUTE, OKAY?

28:54.566 --> 28:57.819
IF YOU NEED ME,
JUST CALL.

28:57.902 --> 28:58.987
THANKS.

29:00.530 --> 29:02.157
[ DOOR OPENS ]

29:02.240 --> 29:04.075
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

29:05.410 --> 29:07.162
[ SIGHS ]

29:09.789 --> 29:11.916
I KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE THINKING, MAMA.

29:12.000 --> 29:14.210
BUT I HAD TO LIE
ABOUT GRADY BEING DEAD

29:14.294 --> 29:16.546
SO THAT WESLEY
WOULD TELL ME THE TRUTH.

29:17.422 --> 29:18.715
THAT'S MY JOB.

29:18.798 --> 29:21.926
AND YOU HAD TO LIE
TO YOUR FATHER AND ME, TOO.

29:22.010 --> 29:25.054
WE DROVE ALL THE WAY
ACROSS THE COUNTRY

29:25.138 --> 29:26.639
FEELING JUST HORRIBLE

29:26.723 --> 29:29.184
ABOUT THE MURDER
OF A YOUNG BOY

29:29.267 --> 29:32.604
WHO IS FAST ASLEEP
ON YOUR SOFA.

29:41.362 --> 29:42.822
[ DISHES CLANKING ]

29:44.741 --> 29:45.950
[ EXHALES DEEPLY ]

29:49.621 --> 29:51.998
IF I HAD TOLD
YOU AND DADDY THE TRUTH,

29:52.081 --> 29:54.709
YOU WOULD HAVE
TREATED WESLEY DIFFERENTLY,

29:54.792 --> 29:57.712
AND THEN HE MIGHT HAVE FIGURED
OUT THAT I WAS LYING TO HIM,

29:57.795 --> 29:59.380
AND THEN
HE WOULDN'T HAVE CONFESSED.

29:59.464 --> 30:02.550
AND I'M SORRY IF YOUR FEELINGS
GOT HURT, BUT WHAT I DID

30:02.634 --> 30:04.928
WILL HELP BRING TWO MURDERERS
IN OFF THE STREETS,

30:05.011 --> 30:06.513
AND THAT HAS TO BE
WORTH SOMETHING.

30:06.596 --> 30:07.764
WORTH --

30:07.847 --> 30:11.476
WORTH PUTTING WESLEY
THROUGH FOUR DAYS OF HELL,

30:11.559 --> 30:13.728
MAKING HIM FEEL RESPONSIBLE
FOR THE DEATH

30:13.811 --> 30:17.565
OF THE ONE PERSON HE
LOVED MORE THAN ANYONE
ELSE IN THE WORLD?

30:20.485 --> 30:22.862
YOU FEEL SO SORRY
FOR WESLEY.

30:27.825 --> 30:28.910
WHAT ABOUT
THESE TWO MEN?

30:28.993 --> 30:31.829
ARNIE GILLON
AND JIMMY HAYES.

30:31.913 --> 30:33.915
TWO FAMILIES ARE GONNA HAVE
AN EMPTY SEAT AT THE TABLE

30:33.998 --> 30:36.417
FOR CHRISTMAS DINNER THIS YEAR
BECAUSE OF WHAT WESLEY DID.

30:38.586 --> 30:41.965
TALK TO THE GILLONS
OR JIMMY'S MOM.

30:42.048 --> 30:45.927
SEE HOW THEY FEEL ABOUT
HOW AWFUL I WAS TO WESLEY.

30:46.010 --> 30:47.095
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

30:47.178 --> 30:48.680
EXCUSE ME, CHIEF.

30:48.763 --> 30:49.931
UM...SPEAKING OF WESLEY,

30:50.014 --> 30:52.308
HE APPARENTLY
JUST DUMPED HIS WIRE.

30:52.392 --> 30:53.768
ROSS LOST HIM.

30:55.895 --> 30:58.106
I WANT TWO SQUAD CARS
OUTSIDE OF THIS HOUSE RIGHT NOW

30:58.189 --> 31:01.359
AND SOMEONE FROM S.I.S.,
AND AS SOON AS THEY GET HERE,

31:01.442 --> 31:03.611
I WANT YOU TO COME BACK
TO THE MURDER ROOM, OKAY?

31:03.695 --> 31:05.405
THANK YOU.

31:05.488 --> 31:06.990
MAMA...

31:08.700 --> 31:10.952
I FEEL TERRIBLE ABOUT
HOW I HAD TO TREAT WESLEY.

31:11.035 --> 31:12.620
BUT JUST KNOW --

31:12.704 --> 31:16.249
IF I HAD TO DO IT
ALL OVER AGAIN...

31:16.332 --> 31:18.293
I WOULDN'T
CHANGE A THING.

31:26.259 --> 31:28.344
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

31:34.183 --> 31:36.227
[ SNIFFLES ]

31:44.402 --> 31:47.155
[<i> EXHALES DEEPLY, SNIFFS</i> ]

31:47.238 --> 31:48.698
<i>HEY, BRENDA.</i>

31:48.781 --> 31:50.241
[<i> CLEARS THROAT</i> ]

31:50.325 --> 31:52.535
<i>UH, I WATCHED THAT</i>
<i>CRIME-SCENE TAPE YOU SHOWED ME,</i>

31:52.619 --> 31:53.870
<i>AND YOU KNOW WHAT?</i>

31:53.953 --> 31:55.997
<i>IT SHOWED HOW</i>
<i>R.J. AND THUMPS BROKE IN</i>

31:56.080 --> 31:59.542
<i>AND HOW THEY KILLED GRADY</i>
<i>LOOKING FOR THE MONEY.</i>

31:59.626 --> 32:01.169
<i>HERE'S THE THING --</i>

32:01.252 --> 32:03.671
<i>R.J. AND THUMPS KNEW</i>
<i>WHERE MY MONEY WAS ALL ALONG,</i>

32:03.755 --> 32:05.715
<i>JUST LIKE I KNEW</i>
<i>WHERE THEY KEPT THEIRS.</i>

32:05.798 --> 32:08.343
<i>THEY WOULDN'T HAVE NEEDED</i>
<i>TO KILL GRADY.</i>

32:08.426 --> 32:11.179
<i>SO THAT MEANS</i>
<i>I RECKON GRADY'S STILL ALIVE.</i>

32:11.262 --> 32:14.098
<i>UNFORTUNATELY,</i>
<i>THAT MEANS THAT, UH,</i>

32:14.182 --> 32:16.726
<i>GRADY'S THE ONE WHO TOLD YOU</i>
<i>WHO R.J. AND THUMPS ARE.</i>

32:16.809 --> 32:19.187
<i>WELL, THEY'RE GONNA FIGURE THAT</i>
<i>OUT, TOO, WHEN YOU CATCH THEM.</i>

32:19.270 --> 32:20.855
<i>THEY'RE NOT GONNA LIKE IT,</i>
<i>EITHER.</i>

32:20.938 --> 32:22.190
<i>SEE?</i>

32:22.273 --> 32:24.942
<i>THIS TIME,</i>
<i>I'M NOT RUNNING AWAY.</i>

32:25.026 --> 32:26.569
<i>AND, UH...</i>

32:26.653 --> 32:30.281
<i>IF THINGS</i>
<i>DON'T WORK OUT FOR ME...</i>

32:30.365 --> 32:34.243
<i>LOOK AFTER MY LITTLE BROTHER,</i>
<i>WILL YA?</i>

32:34.327 --> 32:36.579
<i>AND, UH...</i>

32:36.663 --> 32:40.416
<i>SAY THANKS</i>
<i>TO YOUR MOM AND DAD FOR...</i>

32:40.500 --> 32:43.294
<i>FOR BEING SO NICE TO ME</i>
<i>AND ALL.</i>

32:46.214 --> 32:49.008
<i>HOPE YOU GET</i>
<i>THIS MESSAGE HERE.</i>

32:49.884 --> 32:53.721
<i>OKAY. GOT TO RUN.</i>

33:00.520 --> 33:01.813
HOW'D WE FIND THE WIRE?

33:01.896 --> 33:04.065
WESLEY CALLED IT IN HIMSELF
THREE HOURS AGO.

33:04.148 --> 33:06.109
TOLD US WHERE TO LOOK.
SANCHEZ PICKED IT UP.

33:06.192 --> 33:09.987
AFTER WE DOWNLOADED THE CAMERA,
I THOUGHT YOU SHOULD SEE THIS.

33:11.781 --> 33:14.909
WHAT ARE WE
LOOKING AT NOW?

33:14.992 --> 33:16.411
COASTAL
PACIFIC SAVINGS --

33:16.494 --> 33:18.287
TWO BLOCKS
FROM THE SANTA ANA FREEWAY.

33:18.371 --> 33:20.456
HE LEFT THE CAMERA RIGHT
ACROSS THE STREET FROM IT.

33:20.540 --> 33:22.417
THAT'S -- THAT'S NOT ONE
OF THE BANKS WE'RE COVERING.

33:22.500 --> 33:23.793
IT WASN'T
ON WESLEY'S ROUTE.

33:23.876 --> 33:25.086
WELL,
IT WAS ON ARNIE GILLON'S,

33:25.169 --> 33:28.548
AND THERE'S ABOUT $400,000
ON BOARD.

33:28.631 --> 33:29.882
Pope: ROBBERY/HOMICIDE
IS LEADING

33:29.966 --> 33:31.759
EIGHT-MAN TEAMS
AT FOUR OTHER BANKS,

33:31.843 --> 33:33.386
S.I.S. IS FULLY DEPLOYED,

33:33.469 --> 33:35.138
AND<i> NOBODY</i>
IS IN THE RIGHT PLACE?

33:35.221 --> 33:36.723
ARE YOU SURE?

33:36.806 --> 33:39.058
IN ADDITION TO THE WIRE THAT
WE PUT ON FOR DETECTIVE ROSS,

33:39.142 --> 33:41.436
WE ALSO EMBEDDED TRANSMITTERS
IN WESLEY'S SHOES.

33:41.519 --> 33:43.479
THE GPS CAN'T GET
A PRECISE LOCATION,

33:43.563 --> 33:45.606
BUT WE'VE BEEN TRACKING HIM
ALL NIGHT LONG.

33:45.690 --> 33:47.442
FIRST OF ALL, HE MUST HAVE
OBTAINED A VEHICLE.

33:47.525 --> 33:49.402
THEN HE DROVE INTO
THE PARK LA BREA APARTMENTS.

33:49.485 --> 33:50.737
MAYBE LOOKING
FOR R.J. AND THUMPS.

33:50.820 --> 33:52.447
MAYBE GOING
TO PICK UP A STASH GUN.

33:52.530 --> 33:54.282
Tao: BUT THEN HE DID
SOMETHING STRANGE --

33:54.365 --> 33:56.117
HE WENT BACK
TO COASTAL PACIFIC.

33:56.200 --> 33:57.952
WHERE HE DROPPED THE WIRE.
THAT WASN'T AN ACCIDENT.

33:58.035 --> 34:00.329
I HAVE UNDERCOVER OFFICERS
LOOKING FOR HIM RIGHT NOW.

34:00.413 --> 34:04.000
WESLEY HAS A RADIUS OF MORE THAN
100 YARDS IN WHICH TO HIDE.

34:04.083 --> 34:07.128
YOU PUT TRANSMITTERS
ON THIS KID BEFORE YOU
HANDED HIM OFF TO ROSS,

34:07.211 --> 34:10.298
SO YOU OBVIOUSLY SUSPECTED
HE MIGHT DO SOMETHING LIKE THIS.

34:10.381 --> 34:11.758
YOU HAD YOUR DOUBTS
ABOUT THE CONFESSION.

34:11.841 --> 34:13.384
NO. THE CONFESSION WAS GOOD.
IT HAD GAPS.

34:13.468 --> 34:14.635
I WAS JUST
COVERING OUR BASES.

34:14.719 --> 34:15.970
Taylor: LOOK, SIR.

34:16.053 --> 34:19.223
IF WESLEY WANTED TO DEAL
WITH THUMPS AND R.J. HIMSELF

34:19.307 --> 34:20.725
AND SAVE US THE TIME
AND THE ENERGY --

34:20.808 --> 34:22.310
THAT WAS NOT MY STRATEGY,
COMMANDER.

34:22.393 --> 34:25.021
I WAS PROVIDING EMERGENCY BACKUP
IN CASE IT WAS NEEDED.

34:25.104 --> 34:28.107
AND OBVIOUSLY IT<i> IS.</i>

34:28.191 --> 34:30.943
LOOK, HAVE YOUR TEAM VEST UP
AND GET TO THIS BANK.

34:35.156 --> 34:37.325
PUT YOUR BEST SHOT ON THE ROOF
AND OUT OF SIGHT.

34:37.408 --> 34:38.951
HAVE HIM PREPARE
TO TAKE OUT THESE KILLERS

34:39.035 --> 34:41.162
THE MOMENT
THEY DRAW THEIR WEAPONS.

34:44.207 --> 34:46.292
Brenda: Any change
in Wesley's whereabouts?

34:46.375 --> 34:47.543
NO MOVEMENT, CHIEF.

34:49.086 --> 34:52.507
BUT I DO SEE
AN ASTRO VAN.

34:52.590 --> 34:54.842
HERE COMES PROVENZA.

34:54.926 --> 34:56.135
Pope:
LOOK AROUND THE TARGET AREA,

34:56.219 --> 34:57.970
BUT AS INCONSPICUOUSLY
AS POSSIBLE.

34:58.054 --> 35:00.097
IF R.J. AND THUMPS DO INTEND
TO ROB THE PLACE,

35:00.181 --> 35:02.558
WE DON'T WANT TO TIP THEM OFF
THAT WE'RE THERE.

35:04.769 --> 35:06.062
THANK YOU.

35:06.145 --> 35:08.356
INFORM THE BANK SO THAT
CUSTOMERS ARE NOT LET OUT

35:08.439 --> 35:11.192
DURING THE PERIOD RIGHT BEFORE
AND AFTER THE TRUCK UNLOADS.

35:11.275 --> 35:15.071
I DON'T WANT
ANY MORE INNOCENT PEOPLE SHOT.

35:15.154 --> 35:16.697
SEARCH THE AREA FOR WESLEY.

35:16.781 --> 35:18.533
IF HE'S NOT MOVING,
HE HAS TO BE HIDING SOMEWHERE.

35:18.616 --> 35:19.992
FIND HIM.

35:20.076 --> 35:22.370
GET RIGHT ON TOP OF ANYBODY
WHO SEEMS VULNERABLE.

35:22.453 --> 35:26.791
DON'T LEAVE ANYONE IN THE OPEN
UNPROTECTED.

35:29.544 --> 35:31.337
SANCHEZ IS IN POSITION.

35:38.511 --> 35:40.847
ALL RIGHT,
THE CAR'S COMING TOWARDS US.

35:40.930 --> 35:42.598
CHIEF, THIS IS IT.

35:44.475 --> 35:46.227
Brenda: We want to catch them
in the act.

35:46.310 --> 35:48.312
We don't want a gunfight
if it can be avoided.

35:48.396 --> 35:52.316
Let's take them down
with as little mess as possible.

35:56.696 --> 35:57.905
GO AHEAD.

36:01.576 --> 36:03.995
Wait for it.

36:04.078 --> 36:05.705
WAIT FOR IT.

36:15.965 --> 36:17.800
[ SHOTGUN COCKS ]

36:21.804 --> 36:23.181
GET ON THE FLOOR!
ON THE FLOOR!

36:23.264 --> 36:25.600
GET ON THE FLOOR!

36:25.683 --> 36:26.601
ON THE GROUND!

36:26.684 --> 36:27.977
GET ON THE GROUND!

36:28.060 --> 36:29.312
WESLEY!

36:33.482 --> 36:35.276
WESLEY, DROP YOUR GUN!

36:35.359 --> 36:36.944
DROP YOUR GUN, WESLEY!

36:37.028 --> 36:38.112
GET AWAY FROM THE CAR.

36:38.195 --> 36:40.114
WESLEY,
ON THE GROUND NOW!

36:40.197 --> 36:41.324
DROP YOUR WEAPON, MAN!

36:41.407 --> 36:42.491
WESLEY!

36:52.877 --> 36:54.420
[ GASPS ]

37:00.509 --> 37:01.677
HOLSTER YOUR GUN!

37:01.761 --> 37:03.346
L.A.P.D.!
DROP YOUR WEAPON!

37:03.429 --> 37:04.805
DROP YOUR GUN!

37:04.889 --> 37:05.681
L.A.P.D.!

37:05.765 --> 37:06.891
DROP YOUR WEAPON!

37:06.974 --> 37:08.392
PUT YOUR WEAPON
ON THE GROUND NOW!

37:08.476 --> 37:09.560
NOW!

37:10.686 --> 37:12.313
GOD!

37:12.396 --> 37:14.523
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

37:47.264 --> 37:51.686
WELL, YOUR PANTS MAY NEED
TAKEN UP A LITTLE.

37:51.769 --> 37:54.355
I-IT'S ALL SO MUCH --
THESE, UH, THESE PRESENTS.

37:54.438 --> 37:56.232
I-I DON'T KNOW
IF I CAN KEEP IT.

37:56.315 --> 37:59.193
WELL, BRENDA AND I
MADE SOME EXTRA MONEY
SELLING THE BUNGALOW,

37:59.277 --> 38:01.570
AND SHE WAS AFRAID WE MIGHT HAVE
A LITTLE LEFT OVER.

38:01.654 --> 38:03.906
WELL, WHEN I SEE WES AGAIN,
I'LL BE SURE TO ASK HIM

38:03.990 --> 38:05.658
IF IT'S OKAY
IF I KEEP EVERYTHING.

38:08.119 --> 38:10.538
I KNOW HE'S DOING IMPORTANT WORK
FOR THE POLICE,

38:10.621 --> 38:14.000
BUT DO YOU THINK MAYBE HE'LL --
HE'LL CALL ME TODAY?

38:14.083 --> 38:16.460
WES?

38:16.544 --> 38:21.173
THAT'S SOMETHING
YOU'LL HAVE TO TALK
TO BRENDA LEIGH ABOUT.

38:21.257 --> 38:21.799
BRENDA!

38:21.882 --> 38:22.842
GRADY.

38:22.925 --> 38:25.219
GRADY,
ASK HER AT THE RESTAURANT.

38:25.302 --> 38:28.723
RIGHT NOW, WE GOT TO GET GOING.
RESERVATION'S AT 1:00.

38:28.806 --> 38:31.809
I CAN'T BELIEVE I WON'T BE
COOKING CHRISTMAS DINNER.

38:31.892 --> 38:33.728
BRENDA! COME ON!

38:33.811 --> 38:36.564
OH, DO YOU THINK
THIS FANCY BEACH HOTEL

38:36.647 --> 38:40.568
WOULD MIND
VALETING AN R.V.?

38:40.651 --> 38:43.571
I WOULD LOVE TO SEE THEM
VALET THE R.V., WILLIE RAY.

38:43.654 --> 38:44.697
LET'S TAKE IT.

38:44.780 --> 38:45.781
[ CHUCKLES ]

38:45.865 --> 38:48.075
BRENDA! COME ON!

38:48.159 --> 38:49.535
Y'ALL ARE BEING TOO NICE,
YOU KNOW?

38:51.495 --> 38:54.707
WESLEY --
HE MUST BE, UH...

38:54.790 --> 38:57.376
MUST BE SOME KIND OF HERO,
RIGHT?

38:58.377 --> 39:01.756
IN HIS OWN WAY, YES.

39:01.839 --> 39:04.050
AND I THINK NOW
FOR THE REST OF THE DAY,

39:04.133 --> 39:08.179
WE SHOULD ALL CONCENTRATE
ON HAVING A MERRY CHRISTMAS.

39:08.262 --> 39:10.014
ALL RIGHT?

39:17.855 --> 39:18.606
[ SIGHS ]

39:18.689 --> 39:20.274
I'LL TALK TO HER.

39:31.368 --> 39:32.912
[ SIGHS ]

39:40.044 --> 39:41.462
BRENDA.

39:43.380 --> 39:44.924
[ KITTY MEOWS ]

39:45.007 --> 39:46.467
I'M -- I'M NOT
QUITE READY, OKAY?

39:46.550 --> 39:48.219
I JUST --
I JUST NEED ONE MINUTE.

39:48.302 --> 39:49.762
IF YOU DON'T
PULL IT ALL TOGETHER,

39:49.845 --> 39:53.140
GRADY'S GONNA THINK
SOMETHING'S WRONG.

39:53.224 --> 39:55.518
SOMETHING<i> IS</i> WRONG,
DADDY.

39:55.601 --> 39:57.478
I'M GONNA HAVE TO
TELL THAT BOY TOMORROW

39:57.561 --> 39:58.813
THAT HIS BROTHER'S DEAD.

39:58.896 --> 40:00.231
NO, YOU DO NOT.

40:00.314 --> 40:01.649
YOU'RE GONNA TELL HIM

40:01.732 --> 40:04.819
THAT WESLEY IS WORKING
WITH THE POLICE UNDERCOVER

40:04.902 --> 40:08.656
UNTIL THE KID GETS USED TO
NOT SEEING HIM.

40:08.739 --> 40:11.200
HOW MUCH LONGER DO YOU THINK
GRADY'S GONNA BELIEVE THAT?

40:11.283 --> 40:13.661
YOU TOLD YOUR MOTHER
YOU WERE A PROFESSIONAL LIAR.

40:13.744 --> 40:15.746
I THINK YOU COULD
FIGURE SOMETHING OUT

40:15.830 --> 40:18.582
TO TELL HIM,
MAKE HIM BELIEVE IT.

40:18.666 --> 40:20.626
[ SIGHS ]

40:20.709 --> 40:22.503
YOU...

40:22.586 --> 40:24.255
YOU HAVE A TOUGH JOB.

40:25.422 --> 40:28.342
YOU HAVE TO MAKE
HARD DECISIONS.

40:28.425 --> 40:31.011
BUT I GUESS
IF I WOULD TRUST ANYBODY

40:31.095 --> 40:34.306
WITH MAKING
HARD DECISIONS,

40:34.390 --> 40:37.017
IT WOULD BE
MY LITTLE GIRL.

40:40.104 --> 40:42.773
I TRY TO DO
WHAT'S RIGHT.

40:42.857 --> 40:44.275
I DO.

40:44.358 --> 40:46.443
TO THE VERY BEST
OF MY ABILITY.

40:49.113 --> 40:50.489
[ SIGHS ]

40:50.573 --> 40:56.078
WHEN YOU'RE PACKING UP
THIS PLACE TOMORROW...

40:56.162 --> 40:58.080
WE'LL PART COMPANY.

40:58.164 --> 41:02.168
YOUR MOTHER AND I WANT
TO TAKE GRADY WITH US.

41:02.251 --> 41:05.588
WE'LL TELL HIM IT'S
A WITNESS-PROTECTION PROGRAM

41:05.671 --> 41:07.339
OR SOMETHING LIKE THAT.

41:09.425 --> 41:10.759
WESLEY WAS RIGHT.

41:12.636 --> 41:15.681
HE TOLD ME
TO SAY THANK YOU...

41:15.764 --> 41:19.518
TO MY MOM AND MY DAD.

41:19.602 --> 41:22.855
HE ALSO TOLD ME
HOW LUCKY I AM TO HAVE YOU.

41:22.938 --> 41:24.106
AND I<i> AM.</i>

41:24.190 --> 41:26.108
[ Voice breaking ]
GOD, I AM SO LUCKY.

41:28.569 --> 41:31.864
ARE YOU SURE
YOU WANT TO DO THIS, DADDY?

41:31.947 --> 41:33.407
WITH GRADY?

41:33.490 --> 41:37.411
HE'S A GEORGIA BOY,
AND HE'S A MINOR.

41:37.494 --> 41:40.873
WE DON'T WANT HIM
ENDING UP LIKE HIS BROTHER.

41:40.956 --> 41:44.460
SO, YES. WE'RE SURE.

41:44.543 --> 41:46.587
NOW, THEN...

41:46.670 --> 41:48.923
I WANT YOU TO PUT A SMILE
ON YOUR FACE

41:49.006 --> 41:50.758
AND A SPRING
IN YOUR STEP.

41:50.841 --> 41:52.718
IT'S A HOLIDAY,
DAMN IT.

41:52.801 --> 41:54.428
[ CHUCKLES ]

41:54.511 --> 41:56.597
OH, AND, UH...

41:56.680 --> 41:58.349
WHEN YOU GET
TO THAT R.V.,

41:58.432 --> 42:02.519
THERE BETTER BE
SOME PERRY COMO CDs SOMEWHERE.

42:02.603 --> 42:06.440
YOU'RE NOT THE ONLY ONE
THAT'S HAVING A HARD TIME

42:06.523 --> 42:09.360
GETTING IN
THE CHRISTMAS SPIRIT.

42:11.195 --> 42:14.114
WE'LL MEET YOU
OUT FRONT.

42:14.198 --> 42:17.243
[ "O COME, ALL YE FAITHFUL"
INSTRUMENTAL PLAYS ]

42:22.623 --> 42:24.541
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

42:24.625 --> 42:25.918
OH.

42:26.001 --> 42:27.878
[ SIGHS ]

42:40.474 --> 42:41.600
UGH.

42:45.479 --> 42:47.231
[ SIGHS ]
